                        <interp inst="t18790113-name-212" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT LAMBERT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a commission agent at Watford—I am acquainted with the two prisoners Reeves—I know their handwriting—I have seen them write—the letter G 1 is Francis Reeves's writing—the memorandum K 8 I got through them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. FRITH</hi>. I have seen Edmund write many times, Francis seldom, several times—I have known them five years, and have known nothing against them—as far as I knew they were honourable and upright gentlemen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Re-examined.</hi> I have occasionally corresponded with them—I have re<lb></lb>ceived letters from them, and have written to them.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187901130060"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18790113-name-213" type="witnessName">
